https://leetcode.com/problems/toeplitz-matrix/description/


QUESTION:
Input: matrix = [[1,2,3,4],[5,1,2,3],[9,5,1,2]]
Output: true

SOLUTION:
2 optimal approaches:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
class Solution {
    public boolean isToeplitzMatrix(int[][] matrix) {
        for(int i=1;i<matrix.length;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<matrix[0].length;j++){
                if(matrix[i-1][j-1]!=matrix[i][j])return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Follow up question:
If the matrix is huge and i am not able to save all the values in memory then how to implement

Ans: Just save the previous element values in the matrix and then compare.

class Solution {
    public boolean isToeplitzMatrix(int[][] matrix) {
        int prev[]=matrix[0];
        for(int i=1;i<matrix.length;i++){
            int curr[]=matrix[i];
            for(int j=1;j<matrix[0].length;j++){
                if(curr[j]!=prev[j-1])return false;
            }
            prev=curr;
        }
        return true;
    }
}
